/*
Solution Explanation:

Notice that every digit except 1 expands each time. 

You cannot brute force the solution because:
1. The string gets way too long (MLE)
2. Your program cannot run in time (TLE)

To solve this problem, you need to make the following key observation: 
If the string doesn't contain the digit 1, then the answer will be the first digit. 
This is because the digits expand exponentially. 
After 10^10 seconds, even the smallest digit 2 will have an amount of 2^(10^10), 
which is 100% more than the upper bound of the x constraint (pay attention to constraints, as they might help you sometimes).

But what about having 1 in the string? 
It becomes extremely clear how to solve this if you had the key observation. 
If x is larger than the length of s, then the answer must be the first non-one digit. 
This is because 1 cannot expand after any number of seconds, 
so having x larger than the length of s guarantees the existence of a non-one digit. 
Otherwise, simply loop through all the digits up to the x index (remember, x is 1-indexed) 
and check if there is a non-one digit. If there is, then after 10^10 seconds, 
the x index must be that digit. If not, the answer is 1.

Hope you had fun solving this problem! :D
*/
#include <iostream>
#include <string>
#include <vector>
#include <algorithm>
using namespace std;
using ll = long long; using str = string;
#define up(initial, n, step) for(ll i = (ll)(initial);i < (ll)(n);i+=(ll)(step))
int main(void){
    ios::sync_with_stdio(0);cin.tie(0);cout.tie(0);
    ll n, x; str s;
    cin >> n >> s >> x;
    if (x <= s.length()) {
        ll allOne = 1;
        up(0, x, 1) if (s[i] != '1') { allOne = 0; break; }
        if (allOne) {cout << 1 << '\n'; return EXIT_SUCCESS;}
    }
    up(0, n, 1) if (s[i] != '1') { cout << s[i] << '\n'; break; }
    return EXIT_SUCCESS;
}
